# Documentation Standards

## When to Update Docs
- New or changed routes (`src/routes/index.tsx`)
- New env vars (`VITE_*`)
- Auth/OIDC/MFA/WebAuthn/federation behavior changes
- New API integrations (admin console, settings)
- Production deployment changes (`deploy/Caddyfile`)

## What to Document

### README.md (primary)
- Setup: `make setup`, `make run`
- Route table when adding pages
- Env var table in `.env.example` — keep in sync
- Backend alignment table (proxy, OIDC login URL, WebAuthn origins)

### .env.example
- All `VITE_*` vars with safe defaults and comments
- No secrets or production credentials

### API types
- Update `src/api/types.ts` when backend DTOs change
- Optional: `make generate-api` if openapi-typescript is configured

### Backend docs (cross-repo)
When frontend behavior depends on backend changes, note in PR and update backend docs if you own that change:
- [backend/docs/README.md](../backend/docs/README.md) — hub
- [backend/docs/features/](../backend/docs/features/) — feature behavior
- [backend/docs/testing/](../backend/docs/testing/) — curl flows

## Style
- Concise and practical — include real commands (`make run`, URLs with ports)
- Verify paths exist in this repo
- Outdated docs are worse than no docs
